:16px;line-height:30px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;list-style-type:square;=
mso-special-format:bullet"><li><i>Taylor=E2=80=99s Version</i>: This week, =
former <i>New York Times</i> and <i>Washington Post</i> journalist <b>Taylo=
r Lorenz </b>came under fire for ostensibly celebrating the murder of <b>Br=
ian Thompson</b>, the UnitedHealthcare C.E.O. who was shot and killed in Ma=
nhattan on Wednesday. =E2=80=9CAnd people wonder why we want these executiv=
es dead,=E2=80=9D Lorenz, stunningly, wrote on social media. She also share=
d celebratory graphics relating to the murder of the 50-year-old father of =
two, and posted the full name, title, and headshot of another health insura=
nce executive. Lorenz later wrote an essay <u><a href=3D"https://email.puck=
=2Enews/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1l=
EQUt2UktxclJLZ0dUbnBQcmJudFhnZHFrN2FhQ=
1J5Zz0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubWVkaWFpdGUuY29tL25ld3MvdGF5bG9yLWxvcmVu=
ei1kZWZlbmRzLWhlci1jZWxlYnJhdGlvbi1vZi1icmlhbi10aG9tcHNvbnMtbXVyZGVyLWl0cy1=
uYXR1cmFsLz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249SW4rdGhlK1Jvb20rLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMiUyRj=
YlMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PUluK1RoZStSb29tKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4M=
TIlMkY2JTJGMjQlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3Vy=
Y2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5=
hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwMDkyODB9/75118a76820e98950=
63d1d1711d8359e078eb5eb694021328840bd8c6b129951" style=3D"color:#d40000;tex=
t-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sdf">defending herself</a></u>=
 against the =E2=80=9Cpearl-clutching=E2=80=9D outrage of her critics.<br/>=
<br/>I=E2=80=99m not here to weigh in on the grotesqueness of celebrating m=
urder=E2=80=94Lorenz=E2=80=99s reputation precedes her=E2=80=94but it is in=
teresting to see her show her true character after the <i>Times</i> and the=
n the <i>Post</i> invested so much time and energy trying to defend that re=
putation. As I=E2=80=99ve reported, the <i>Post</i> severed ties with Loren=
z in early October, graciously allowing her to =E2=80=9Cresign to pursue a =
career in independent journalism=E2=80=9D after it determined that she=E2=
=80=99d misled them about a social post she shared in which <b>President
Biden</b> was labeled as =E2=80=9Ca war criminal.=E2=80=9D (Lorenz disputes=
 this account of her departure.) When the <i>Post</i> first began investiga=
ting the matter, in August, Lorenz appeared to claim that her post had been=
 doctored: =E2=80=9CYou people will fall for any dumbass edit someone makes=
